x4freetext: Neutron resonance parameters of bromine-79 and
operated at 30 and 80 ns pulse width and 300PPS
Separated isotopes in the chemical form of NaBr from
at 47.08 and 190 m flight stations. Flux monitored
A 3.8 cm dia. x 1.27 cm thick 6Li glass
photomultiplier, was used for transmission measurements
carried out using a 190 m flight path and a set of six
12 cm dia.x l.27 cm thick 6Li-glass scintillators to
Moxon-Rae detector was used for capture
Neutron energy scale was calibrated with the
For multiple scattering by Monte Carlo and for
A.P.T. Japan code changed to JPN
Added SUBENTs with cross sections, received
from the author. The letters are changed on small.
SD: REACTION code changed to sum of
reactions in Subents 10-18 following remark of M.Ohkubo
via N.Otsuka. Small corrections in all Subents.
